<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Python for Chemists workshops</title>
  <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/szczypinski-group/python-for-chemists/954f82c2a62a5ced59e9717015a45d9252a52599/public/favicon.svg">
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #333;
      background-color: #fff;
      padding: 20px;
      margin: 0;
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 1000px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    header {
      background-color: #f0f0f0;
      padding: 20px;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    .logo {
      height: 80px;
      width: auto;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: 24px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .subtitle {
      font-size: 16px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    .section-title {
      font-size: 20px;
      margin: 20px 0 10px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .cards {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 20px;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }
    .card {
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
      border: 1px solid #ddd;
      flex: 1 0 200px;
    }
    .card-header {
      background-color: #ddd;
      padding: 10px;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    .card-header.app {
      background-color: #eee;
    }
    .card-body {
      padding: 15px;
    }
    .card-link {
      display: inline-block;
      background-color: #4a86e8;
      color: white;
      padding: 5px 10px;
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    .card-link.app {
      background-color: #ff9900;
    }
    footer {
      background-color: #f0f0f0;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 20px 0;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }
    .footer-links a {
      color: #4a86e8;
      margin: 0 10px;
      text-decoration: none;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body class="font-sans max-w-2xl mx-auto p-8 leading-relaxed">    
    <header>
      <div class="container">
	<img src="https://www.durham.ac.uk/media/durham-university/site-assets/image/logo-dark.svg" alt="Durham logo" class="logo">
        <h1>Python for Chemistry</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Interactive Python notebooks for introductory workshops</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">

    {% if notebooks %}
    <h2 class="section-title">Workshop notebooks</h2>
    <p>Interactive notebooks in edit mode - you can modify and experiment with the code. Note that these <b>live in your browser</b> so make sure to save the outputs somewhere on your computer if you want to keep them!</p>
    <div class="cards">
      {% for notebook in notebooks | sort(attribute='display_name') %}
      <!-- {{ notebook.display_name }} Notebook -->
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header">{{ notebook.display_name }}</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <a href="{{ notebook.html_path }}" class="card-link">Open Notebook</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    {% endif %}

    {% if apps %}
    <h2 class="section-title">Apps</h2>
    <p>Interactive applications in run mode - code is hidden for a clean user interface</p>
    <div class="cards">
      {% for app in apps %}
      <!-- {{ app.display_name }} App -->
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header app">{{ app.display_name }}</div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <a href="{{ app.html_path }}" class="card-link app">Open App</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
    {% endif %}

    <h2 class="section-title">Note on notebooks</h2>
    <p> Python notebooks are often taught to beginners who want to learn coding. Perhaps the most common ones are <a href="https://jupyter.org/" target="_blank">Jupyter Notebooks</a>. In this course, we use <a href="https://marimo.io" target="_blank">marimo</a> for two main reasons: (1) they use reactive execution, meaning there is no hidden state if you execute them in "wrong" order; (2) they are simple Python files, making them better suited for version control with <a href="https://github.com/marimo-team/marimo" target="_blank">GitHub</a>. There are ways of fixing those issues with Jupyter and you are more than welcome to experiment with other platforms in your spare time.</p>
    <p> For these workshop we use Web Assembly (WASM) technology - meaning that the notebooks run in your local browser. If you clear cookies/cache, you will lose the work. For real-world application (including lab reports), I would recommend <a href="https://docs.marimo.io/getting_started/installation/#__tabbed_1_2" target="_blank">installing marimo with uv</a>. For more advanced tasks, like using the popular cheminformatics package <a href="https://www.rdkit.org/docs/index.html" target="_blank">RDKit</a> you would need a local installation too, as they do not work with WASM.</p>

    <h2 class="section-title">Acknowledgements</h2>
    <p> Some of the content is inspired or borrowed from excellent external resources, mainly <a href="https://weisscharlesj.github.io/SciCompforChemists/notebooks/introduction/intro.html" target="_blank">Scientific Computing for Chemist with Python</a> and <a href="https://github.com/Edinburgh-Chemistry-Teaching/Data-driven-chemistry/" target="_blank">Data-driven Chemistry at the University of Edinburgh</a>. Please have a look at their websites for more examples, they are all excellent! </p>
  </main>

    <footer>
      <div class="container">
        <p>Built with <a href="https://marimo.io" target="_blank">marimo</a> - interactive Python notebooks.</p>
        <div class="footer-links">
          <a href="https://github.com/marimo-team/marimo" target="_blank">Marimo GitHub</a>
          <a href="https://docs.marimo.io" target="_blank">Marimo Documentation</a>
	  <a href="https://github.com/szczypinski-group/python-for-chemists" target="_blank">Project GitHub</a>
        </div>
	<p>Code licensed under <a href="https://github.com/marimo-team/marimo/blob/main/LICENSE" target="_blank">Apache License 2.0</a>. Content licensed under <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/deed.en" target="_blank">Creating Commons BY-SA 4.0<a/>.</p>
      </div>
    </footer>

</body>
</html>
